I usually turn garbage collection off, and then explicitly call it just in places where I need to free up memory.  I get a modest 5-10% speed boost from that alone.<p>Another trick is to look at your innermost loops, and make sure you aren&#x27;t doing accessing anything fancier than a variable.<p>Example<p>Bad:<p>for i in onemillionthings:
    for j in onemillionotherthings:
        print SomeClass.otherthing.A<p>Better:
tempvar=SomeClass.otherthing.A
for i in onemillionthings:
    for j in onemillionotherthings:
        print tempvar
